<br>
Scary, isn't it?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>LINK:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=55816">eqlive.station.sony.com/c...p?id=55816</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Anyway here is a short clip of things to look for:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
We've remedied the  long-standing situation that caused characters to lose all their buffs if they zoned with fewer hit points remaining than the bonus hit points provided by their items<br>
<br>
There will be a couple of improvements to Alternate Advancement abilities as well.  We will be giving Beastlords access to the Mass Group Buff ability.  This is an ability that many Beastlords feel would be very useful to them and make some of their buffing tasks a bit easier.  We will also be reducing the reuse timer for the Magician Elemental Form ability from 72 minutes to 15 minutes.  This will allow a Magician to keep the Elemental Form up for as long as he wants.<br>
<br>
Planes of Power has provided us with valuable insight into the group and guild dynamics that are involved in large scale games. The way that we had expected guilds to advance through the story of Planes of Power has become a roadblock for some guilds, and some members have fallen behind and found it difficult to catch up. Obviously this was not our intention. We want players to play with their friends and guild mates.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>To correct this issue, we will be removing the flag requirements for entry into the following Planes of Power zones:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Bastion of Thunder<br>
Plane of Tactics<br>
Halls of Honor<br>
Plane of Nightmare<br>
Plane of Storms<br>
Plane of Torment<br>
Plane of Valor<br>
Crypt of Decay<br>
<br>
This will make the majority of Planes of Power zones available to everyone, and should allow most guilds to travel and adventure together. We understand that those that have already earned the entry flags for these zones have put some effort into that accomplishment. We will be giving a reward to those that have done so, though you'll have to wait to see what that reward is.<br>
<br>
For those that have purchased The Legacy of Ykesha, we added two much requested features to the Guild Management System.  There is now a button on the Guild Management window, named &quot;Dump&quot;, that creates a text file containing all of the information in your Guild Management window.  The file will appear in your EverQuest directory with the name of your guild as the name of the file (with a .txt extension).  Our hope is that this makes updating your guild web pages much easier.  We also added a Show Offline button to the window.  This button determines whether or not you see guildmates that are off line in the window.<br>
<br>
